Description: Oval handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine buff.
Curator's comments: Petrie direw three such pieces (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.31, 35; 32, 13 and 55 42). From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 1103.25
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0518)
